Step 1:  Expand the left-hand side of the equation $(5x^2 - 6x + 7)(4x^2 +tx + 10)$ to obtain an expression in terms of $x$.

$(5x^2 - 6x + 7)(4x^2 +tx + 10) = 20x^4 + (5t - 24)x^3 + (7t + 44)x^2 + (10t - 60)x + 70$
Step 2: 
\begin{align*}
20x^4 + (5t - 24)x^3 + (7t + 44)x^2 + (10t - 60)x + 70 & = 20x^4 -54x^3 +114x^2 -102x +70\\
(5t - 24)x^3 & = -54x^3
\end{align*}
Step 3:
\begin{align*}
(5t - 24)x^3 & = -54x^3\\
5t - 24 & = -54\\
5t & = -54 + 24\\
5t & = -30\\
t & = -30/5\\
t & = -6
\end{align*}
